    {
        "content": "<p><code>Rc</code> is not <code>Send</code> because its reference counting is not thread-safe. If it did and you cloned an <code>Rc</code>, move the clone to another thread, and then start cloning from both threads, the integer holding the reference count will be subject to data races. If your data type does not implement <code>Clone</code> in a way that would adjust <code>Rc</code>'s reference counts, then yeah, you could manually implement <code>Send</code> for your data structure.</p>",
        "id": 229212727,
        "sender_full_name": "nagisa",
        "timestamp": 1615146347
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>They also can't drop from another thread</p>",
